  "description": "EDK (Embedded Development Kit) is a project to enable UEFI support for Virtual Machines. This package contains a sample 64-bit UEFI firmware for QEMU and KVM. \n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* edk2: EDK2: Improper Input Validation allows arbitrary command execution (CVE-2025-2296)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nAdditional Changes:\n\nFor detailed information on changes in this release, see the Rocky Linux 10 Release Notes linked from the References section.",
